snippet: Tiger Woods ran off six straight birdies in the middle of his first-round 64 at the Deutsche Bank Championship, five days after recording his worst round of the year, a 76 at the Barclays.
abstract: Seung-yul Noh takes first-round lead at the Deutsche Bank Championship; Tiger Woods has eight birdies during the first round, but trails the leader by two shots.
lead_paragraph: Tiger Woods ran off six straight birdies in the middle of his first-round 64 at the Deutsche Bank Championship, five days after recording his worst round of the year, a 76 at the Barclays.

headline.seo: Resurgent Tigers Woods Finds a Groove at Deutsche Bank Championship
headline.main: Woods Finds a Groove and Stays There
